Vice President Joe Biden has been appointed by President Barack Obama to oversee the implementation of the provisions in the Recovery Act. Biden will meet regularly with key members of the Cabinet, Governors, and Mayors to ensure that their efforts are efficient and effective. He will also provide regular public reports on implementation, which will be posted on Recovery.gov. Earl Devaney has been appointed as Chair of the Recovery Act Transparency and Accountability Board, reporting to the Vice President. Devaney has a background in law enforcement and has been recognized for his work in pursuing waste, fraud, and mismanagement.